description: NY Pizza Suprema is an Award Winning Pizza place in business in same location a cross from Penn station and MSG for 56 years serving only NY style pizza and no other foods. Featured on The Rachel Ray show, Time Out New York, Good Day New York, The Wall Street Journal and numerous other NY newspapers and periodicals where we routinely make “Best Pizza in NYC” lists. Sliceharvester rated us #1 Pizza Place after sampling close to 400 pizzas in Manhattan pizza places. Recently we have been Honored by The Ellis Island National Museum of Immigration with an Exibit of our pizzeria celebrating the “History of Pizza in America.” We are Celebrity Chef Curtis Stone’s favorite pizza in America. We are rated 8th Best slice of pizza in the World by Big 7 Travel. At NY Pizza Suprema pizza is not just another item on our menu — pizza is all we make! We use 5 different red sauces, use a 30 month aged parmigiano-reggiano, 16 month aged pecorino romano, extra virgin olive oil — all from Italy!

name: Scalini Fedeli
description: Scalini Fedeli ranked among New York's finest restaurants since its opening in early 2004, taking Italian cuisine to new heights. Rewarded with the highest overall ratings in the Zagat Survey, Scalini Fedeli has been granted one star by the Michelin guide in it's inaugural 2006 issue. The inviting decor features vaulted ceilings and European antiques and provides the perfect setting for chef Michael Cetrulo's delightful cuisine which offers the finest ingredients coupled with a confidence and grace that ensures your meal will be a memorable one. Menu highlights include soft egg yolk raviolo with ricotta and truffle butter and New York's finest venison chop in a port wine and balsamic vinegar sauce with toasted hazelnuts, sauteed spinach and roasted Mission figs. The 350-bottle wine list encompasses all regions of Italy but also does justice to the best American wineries.
